# UI and Styling Guidelines

## Styling Approach
- Consistent Styling: Use StyleSheet.create() for consistent styling or Styled Components for dynamic styles
- Create reusable style objects and themes
- Avoid inline styles except for dynamic values
- Use consistent spacing and sizing scales

## Responsive Design
- Responsive Design: Ensure your design adapts to various screen sizes and orientations
- Consider using responsive units and libraries like react-native-responsive-screen
- Use Flexbox for layout management
- Test on multiple screen sizes and orientations
- Consider safe area handling for different devices

## Image Optimization
- Optimize Image Handling: Use optimized image libraries like react-native-fast-image to handle images efficiently
- Use appropriate image formats (WebP when possible)
- Implement proper image caching strategies
- Provide multiple image resolutions for different screen densities

## Design System
- Establish a consistent color palette and typography system
- Create reusable UI components with consistent styling
- Use consistent spacing and layout patterns
- Implement dark mode support when applicable

## Accessibility
- Follow accessibility guidelines for mobile apps
- Use proper semantic elements and roles
- Ensure adequate color contrast
- Provide alternative text for images
- Test with screen readers
